				\begin{document}$$ {D}_{{\mathrm{OH}}^{-}} $$\end{document}DOH− = 4.56 ± 1.29 *10−5 cm2 s−1 (Lee and Rasaiah 2011). Even increasing d by a factor of 10 due to the complex path through the tortuous wall pore geometry and decreasing D by a factor of 10 (an approximation made for small mobile molecules in the cell wall, Kramer et al. 2007), the diffusion time would be of the order of seconds, rather than the observed delay of ~ 15 min.
